This afternoon I was notified that a key DRHS employee tested positive for Covid-19. Consequently I regret to inform you that after careful consideration and discussions the district has made the heartbreaking decision to cancel graduation activities for Saturday, May 16. Please know the decision did not come lightly and I once again apologize for the disappointment. Cross your fingers we can make the July ceremony happen!

Dr. Summer Schultz

Here are the results for the state FCCLA conference competition! The Dell Rapids FCCLA Chapter received the Merit Chapter Award for their overall accomplishments for the year. The following received a Gold rating on their STAR Events: Abby Stauffenecker in Career Investigation, Faithe Larson in Fashion Construction, Desirae Hallem in Professional Presentation, and Rylee Rinehart in Sports Nutrition.

Faithe and Rylee (pictured in this post) now advance to national competition in their respective events this summer.

post_text:
Lunch Count: Week of May 11

Anyone ages 0-18 can participate in the Grab and Go meals from 11:30 am – 12:15 pm in the elementary and middle school lobbies. Please keep in mind suppliers are struggling to provide some items, and we are only able to provide what is shipped. Breakfast items for the next day will be available for pickup with lunches.

If your child is NOT a DPRS student, but will be home alone, I will deliver them a meal. Although our intention was to only deliver to DRPS students, I don’t want any child hungry during this time. Please let your child know to look for Jeff Schmidt or myself.

To assist with planning, please take a survey to provide a head count for meals. The survey should be taken for each child in your family. If you utilize both delivery and pick-up, please take the survey twice for your child and select the appropriate days for each option.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/CQ8SDR5

One, reimbursable lunch will be provided. Additional items not donated will need to be charged to a student’s lunch account.

The Dell Rapids School District has an opening for a full-time custodian at our High School.

Hours: 40 per week / 2:00 PM to 10:30 PM / Mon-Fri - Day hours during summer break

Wage: starting @ $13.50 per hour

Start Date: June 8, 2020

Responsibilities include cleaning classrooms and gym, some snow removal, ability to lift 30 lbs, ability to climb ladders for small maintenance tasks, securing the building, operating small cleaning equipment, and completing minor repairs.

Select https://www.dr-k12.org/Content/dr-custodial to apply!

Anyone wishing to purchase tickets for the Boys State A Basketball Tournament in Rapid City on March 19, 20 and 21, 2020 has 3 options to acquire those tickets. The Dell Rapids School District will NOT be ordering and distributing tickets for fans so tickets must be purchased in one of the following ways:

1) Purchase the tickets at the box office in the Rushmore Plaza Civic Center on the day of the game

2) Go to www.gotmine.com and follow the instructions to secure tickets online.

3) Send your request along with check/payment directly to the Rushmore Plaza Civic Center
at the following address:

Rushmore Plaza Civic Center Box Office
444 Rushmore Road
Rapid City, SD 57701

Tickets are not reserved seats. Costs are $45 for an all-tournament adult pass and $30 for an all-tournament student pass. There are no refunds for these advance tickets

post_text:
The Dell Rapids School District is conducting an E-Learning Feasibility Study. This study will assist efforts to determine our district’s capability to utilize remote learning in the event of an individual student health issue, district-wide health epidemic, weather emergency, etc. We would ask that each family completes a brief, two-question survey (each family was also emailed the survey). The survey will remain open through April 1. If your family has not completed the survey, the link to it is https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/drpselearning.

We appreciate your cooperation and encourage you to reach out if you have questions.

post_text: One of our FFA members in the spotlight! Good job, Mason!
shared_text:
South Dakota FFA Association
February 17 at 8:45 AM ·

This week for our Member Spotlight we are featuring Mason Machmiller.

Mason is from the Dell Rapids FFA Chapter and has been very involved in the FFA organization through his time as a member. Mason has participated in many FFA activities. This includes attending the West-river FFA Leadership Retreat in the summer of 2018 and 2019.

He has also seen many achievements within the organization, one of which include receiving his State FFA Degree.

When Mason was asked why he enjoyed being involved in South Dakota FFA, his response was “I enjoy making a difference in my community and school.” He also said, “I have learned to develop leadership skills and make a positive difference in my chapter by being a chapter officer and motivating my chapter members to achieve success in FFA.”

Mason hasn’t fully decided what he plans to do after high school, but he does plans to attend a 4-year university.

If you want to be featured in our Member Spotlight, contact your FFA Chapter Advisor for the link!

shared_text:
Sonya Darland Weiland‎Dell Rapids School District
February 15 at 1:53 PM ·

For all Quarriers! This year, for the first time in many years, schools have the opportunity to take their ENTIRE wrestling team to the state tournament. The Quarriers are an "A" school along with 32 other schools, including the biggies like all the Sioux Falls schools, Watertown, Aberdeen and all the Rapid City schools. Only the top eight wrestling teams qualify to compete as a team at the state tournament. Currently, your Quarriers are 8th on the list, ahead of many bigger schools. Tonight at 5pm at Roosevelt High School, your Quarrier wrestling team will be dueling both Lincoln and Roosevelt High School. COME SHOW THEM SOME QUARRIER LOVE!! And don't worry if you don't know much about wrestling; it doesn't matter & they would LOVE to have you, or you can come sit by me.
